	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I have the OneStation, a few 8-bit cartridges, 2 "original" 16-bit cartridges, the Mega Drive adaptor, and a few carts for that.
<br />
<br />The 8-bit carts are a mixed bag.  A lot of the no-name 21-in-1 carts just contain crappy HK originals, or licensed FC games hacked beyond recognition.  A few others have a good list of original Famicom/NES releases -- really good ones, like Super C, Snow Bros., and Recca.
<br />
<br />The 16-bit ones are full of strange 16-bit HK originals.  I don't know what kind of processor this thing's running off, but its quality is roughly between MD and SNES.  The games mostly suck, though.
<br />
<br />See here for plenty of screenshots: <a href="http://www.nesworld.com/p8-onestation.htm" class="postlink">http://www.nesworld.com/p8-onestation.htm</a>
<br />
<br />The Mega Drive adaptor and game carts are really great -- tiny portable versions of classics like Strider, Sonic, Sonic 2, etc.  The only downside to the MD adaptor -- and a weird one, at that -- is that the video is output as a 60hz PAL standard.  (It's black and white on my TV, anyway.)

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


